The paper combines reinforcement learning with visual perception, which suggests it could fall under several categories. The use of mid-level perception and feature selection indicates a focus on machine learning and computer vision (cs.LG and cs.CV). The study also involves navigation-oriented tasks, which could fall under robotics (cs.RO) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the use of sample efficiency and state-of-the-art feature learning methods suggests a focus on neural networks (cs.NE).
